
	- Constructor is a special member function/method used to initialize
	objects.
	
	- It is special because its name is same as that of the class.
	
	- It is declared in the public section.
	
	- In case no explicit is defined language compiler/interpreter
	  defines a default constructor.
	  
	Types of constructor:
		- Default/No argument constructor
			public ClassName() {}
		- Parameterized constructor
			public ClassName(int p1, float p2) {...}
		- Copy constructor
			public ClassName(ClassName p) {...}
			
	static keyword
		- normal class methods are called using class objects.
		- whereas static methods are called using class name.
		
	Package: is a way of organising classes in java.
	
	
	Library:
		Standard Library
		Custom Library
		
	Convert amount from figures to words.
	
